        "rich_text_TFQMEM": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Hoop earrings trace their origins back thousands of years. They were first seen in ancient Mesopotamia, Nubia, and Egypt, where both men and women wore gold hoops as symbols of wealth and power. Over centuries, different cultures adapted hoops to reflect their artistry - Greeks and Romans added intricate metalwork, while the Renaissance era saw a decline in their popularity due to elaborate hairstyles that covered the ears.</p><p>By the 1960s and 1970s, hoop earrings made a striking comeback, becoming icons of empowerment and identity, especially within Latina and African-American cultures. In recent decades, their appeal has evolved once again, merging minimalism with opulence in fine jewellery collections such as those found in<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Lucira’s Collections</span></a>.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
